  "texts": [
    "There is evidence that many bodily movements, from complex co-operative behaviours (Miller, 2018) to patterns of gaze direction (Donnarumma et al., 2017) play this role.",
    "The same literature provides reasons to think that cognitive offloading transforms our cognitive repertoire: it allows agents to manifest cognitive abilities that they otherwise would not be able to.",
    "Long division, in which most of us rely on external props of some kind (from traditional pen and paper to a smartphone's calculator 1 3 app), gives one kind of example.",
    "But this literature suggests many more, less obvious ones.",
    "Unaided human information processing is subject to drastic constraints: highcapacity processing of the visual field is limited to a fairly small foveated region, salient features of unattended perceptual stimuli are routinely missed, and working memory can only process a few semantic items at a time (Simons & Levin, 1997; Vogel et al., 2001)."
  ]
}